my dance partner I feel sorry for.

68
00:02:52,660 --> 00:02:53,460
He won't be able to lift me.

69
00:02:54,820 --> 00:02:56,780
Then he'd better work
on his strength training.

70
00:02:56,940 --> 00:02:58,220
That's his problem.

71
00:03:00,780 --> 00:03:01,020
So, how is it?

72
00:03:01,020 --> 00:03:01,380
Delicious.

73
00:03:01,580 --> 00:03:02,860
Come on, have some more.

74
00:03:03,420 --> 00:03:04,020
Ting,

75
00:03:04,540 --> 00:03:05,820
no more news

76
00:03:06,460 --> 00:03:07,420
on the Queen Ballet thing?

77
00:03:10,300 --> 00:03:11,740
That was so long ago.

78
00:03:12,540 --> 00:03:13,660
You're still hung up on it?

79
00:03:13,780 --> 00:03:15,140
To be rejected for a reason like that?

80
00:03:16,220 --> 00:03:17,180
I can't accept it.

81
00:03:21,300 --> 00:03:22,140
It's okay, Dad.

82
00:03:22,980 --> 00:03:24,460
There are plenty of good dance troupes.

83
00:03:26,940 --> 00:03:27,620
Besides,

84
00:03:28,180 --> 00:03:29,580
I never really wanted to
go abroad anyway.

85
00:03:30,740 --> 00:03:33,220
I think my situation now is just fine.

86
00:03:33,500 --> 00:03:34,580
I'm closer to home.

87
00:03:35,100 --> 00:03:36,660
Whenever I crave your cooking,

88
00:03:36,900 --> 00:03:37,900
I can just come back.

89
00:03:40,700 --> 00:03:41,540
The best place

90
00:03:41,700 --> 00:03:43,500
for ballet is Europe.

91
00:03:44,300 --> 00:03:46,140
That's what Ms. Zhuang said

92
00:03:46,260 --> 00:03:46,980
when you started learning ballet.

93
00:03:48,540 --> 00:03:49,060
Ting,

94
00:03:50,420 --> 00:03:52,500
never give up on your dreams.

95
00:03:53,020 --> 00:03:54,020
You should still

96
00:03:54,020 --> 00:03:55,020
look for opportunities to try again.

97
00:03:55,860 --> 00:03:57,100
I didn't raise you

98
00:03:57,100 --> 00:03:59,460
to keep you by my side forever.

99
00:04:00,340 --> 00:04:01,660
I raised you to become

100
00:04:01,940 --> 00:04:03,500
the person you want to be.

101
00:04:05,620 --> 00:04:06,340
Don't worry, Dad.

102
00:04:07,020 --> 00:04:08,260
Eat up. It's not too hot now.

103
00:04:08,260 --> 00:04:09,060
Have some more.

104
00:04:10,260 --> 00:04:10,780
Okay. Thanks.

105
00:04:10,780 --> 00:04:11,340
No problem.

106
00:04:14,060 --> 00:04:15,020
Why did you come?

107
00:04:23,060 --> 00:04:24,740
What? Are you afraid of seeing me?

108
00:04:27,540 --> 00:04:29,060
Is there something
you haven't said to me?

109
00:04:32,260 --> 00:04:32,940
What else is there left

110
00:04:33,580 --> 00:04:34,500
to say between us?

111
00:04:38,380 --> 00:04:38,940
Fine then.

112
00:04:39,900 --> 00:04:40,900
We have nothing left to say.

113
00:04:42,140 --> 00:04:42,860
I'm leaving now.

114
00:04:43,180 --> 00:04:44,260
Tell Ms. Wen.

115
00:04:45,620 --> 00:04:46,300
Suit yourself.

116
00:04:47,220 --> 00:04:48,300
You're upset now?

117
00:04:50,100 --> 00:04:50,820
I'm not.

118
00:04:51,300 --> 00:04:52,580
What we had is in the past.

119
00:04:53,780 --> 00:04:54,580
It's over.

120
00:04:55,780 --> 00:04:56,300
Yeah.

121
00:04:57,620 --> 00:04:58,220
What did you expect?

122
00:05:14,820 --> 00:05:16,220
Let's spread it out a bit more.

123
00:05:16,900 --> 00:05:17,340
Come on.

124
00:05:22,100 --> 00:05:23,180
What do you think?

125
00:05:23,340 --> 00:05:25,180
Is the back a bit too revealing?

126
00:05:25,820 --> 00:05:26,940
Not at all. It looks beautiful.

127
00:05:28,220 --> 00:05:29,140
It really does look nice.

128
00:05:30,540 --> 00:05:33,060
We'll have some new arrivals
in a few days.

129
00:05:33,180 --> 00:05:34,340
You're welcome to come back

130
00:05:34,380 --> 00:05:35,860
and try them if you have time.

131
00:05:36,820 --> 00:05:37,220
Sure.

132
00:05:49,300 --> 00:05:50,180
So that's the story.

133
00:05:50,900 --> 00:05:51,700
I didn't expect her

134
00:05:52,020 --> 00:05:52,980
to come back so suddenly.

135
00:05:53,340 --> 00:05:53,780
Wow, man.

136
00:05:53,780 --> 00:05:55,900
You've been carrying a torch
for over a decade.

137
00:05:55,900 --> 00:05:57,380
You're really hung up on her.

138
00:05:58,420 --> 00:05:59,980
You absolutely have to end up together,

139
00:05:59,980 --> 00:06:01,100
just like these two.

140
00:06:05,460 --> 00:06:05,900
But

141
00:06:05,900 --> 00:06:07,140
you didn't even tell me
about something this big.

142
00:06:07,140 --> 00:06:08,540
You really don't treat me like a friend.

143
00:06:08,820 --> 00:06:09,740
Did you confess your feelings to her?

144
00:06:11,140 --> 00:06:13,220
She doesn't see me that way.

145
00:06:15,620 --> 00:06:17,060
That's normal.

146
00:06:17,220 --> 00:06:18,300
Take Jiao, for example.

147
00:06:18,500 --> 00:06:19,900
She wasn't into me at first either.

148
00:06:20,180 --> 00:06:20,860
But

149
00:06:20,860 --> 00:06:22,620
I was persistent. I never gave up.

150
00:06:22,780 --> 00:06:23,220
So

151
00:06:23,380 --> 00:06:25,020
she married me right after college.

152
00:06:25,260 --> 00:06:26,540
So you need to confess now.

153
00:06:28,620 --> 00:06:29,300
I know,

154
00:06:29,300 --> 00:06:29,860
you're afraid

155
00:06:29,860 --> 00:06:31,620
if you say it,
you two won't be friends anymore.

156
00:06:31,860 --> 00:06:32,860
I'm not trying to be harsh,

157
00:06:33,100 --> 00:06:34,660
but you're really bad at this stuff.

158
00:06:34,660 --> 00:06:35,300
You have to know,

159
00:06:35,420 --> 00:06:36,940
chasing girls requires a thick skin.

160
00:06:36,940 --> 00:06:39,100
Persistence pays off with women.
Go for it!

161
00:06:39,140 --> 00:06:40,060
Alright.

162
00:06:40,500 --> 00:06:41,100
I'm done playing!

163
00:06:41,700 --> 00:06:43,100
You're never any help.

164
00:06:43,380 --> 00:06:44,180
No, Wang Zeyuan.

165
00:06:44,380 --> 00:06:45,940
You really need to
listen to me this time.

166
00:06:51,060 --> 00:06:51,540
Let's see

167
00:06:52,300 --> 00:06:53,580
what your preferred

168
00:06:53,580 --> 00:06:56,220
wedding decoration styles are like.

169
00:06:56,220 --> 00:06:58,860
We have traditional
Chinese banquet style.

170
00:06:58,860 --> 00:07:01,780
And also Western garden style.

171
00:07:02,180 --> 00:07:02,500
And

172
00:07:02,500 --> 00:07:04,060
you can choose

173
00:07:04,060 --> 00:07:05,060
based on the style

174
00:07:05,060 --> 00:07:06,580
of your attire.

175
00:07:07,580 --> 00:07:09,780
Which one is better,
Chinese or Western style?

176
00:07:11,340 --> 00:07:11,860
I'm not sure.

177
00:07:12,420 --> 00:07:13,060
Which do you like?

178
00:07:13,940 --> 00:07:15,540
I've actually been torn.

179
00:07:16,140 --> 00:07:18,820
Personally, I prefer Western style.

180
00:07:18,940 --> 00:07:20,940
I love the idea of walking

181
00:07:21,260 --> 00:07:22,620
under a floral archway
in the wedding dress

182
00:07:22,620 --> 00:07:24,180
with the blue sky and white clouds.

183
00:07:25,060 --> 00:07:25,820
But I also think

184
00:07:25,980 --> 00:07:27,140
Rui's parents

185
00:07:27,140 --> 00:07:28,340
and mine

186
00:07:28,340 --> 00:07:30,380
might prefer

187
00:07:30,780 --> 00:07:32,300
a more traditional banquet.

188
00:07:33,220 --> 00:07:34,780
Ms. Tan, what do you think?

189
00:07:37,100 --> 00:07:37,700
I actually think

190
00:07:37,700 --> 00:07:39,380
whatever the two of you like
matters most.

191
00:07:39,820 --> 00:07:40,580
After all,

192
00:07:40,580 --> 00:07:42,340
it's the most important day
of your lives.

193
00:07:44,420 --> 00:07:45,140
Also, do you have

194
00:07:45,140 --> 00:07:47,540
a preferred hotel?

195
00:07:47,540 --> 00:07:49,300
We work with many hotels,

196
00:07:49,540 --> 00:07:52,220
but it's better
if you have a preference.

197
00:07:57,260 --> 00:07:59,260
These two seem pretty nice.

198
00:07:59,340 --> 00:07:59,780
This one

199
00:08:00,620 --> 00:08:03,420
has good lighting
and an immersive feel.

200
00:08:03,940 --> 00:08:04,300
Yes.

201
00:08:04,380 --> 00:08:05,100
The other one

202
00:08:05,100 --> 00:08:08,460
has a dreamy, starry night sky vibe.

203
00:08:08,460 --> 00:08:09,220
Which one do you like?

204
00:08:12,380 --> 00:08:13,660
They're both good.

205
00:08:16,660 --> 00:08:17,340
Aactually,

206
00:08:17,820 --> 00:08:19,060
I have a small suggestion.

207
00:08:20,300 --> 00:08:22,020
I'm thinking there might be

208
00:08:22,020 --> 00:08:23,300
many children attending the wedding.

209
00:08:24,100 --> 00:08:25,620
If we could

210
00:08:25,740 --> 00:08:27,900
set up a kids' play area
somewhere nearby,

211
00:08:28,060 --> 00:08:29,260
the children would have a place to go

212
00:08:29,540 --> 00:08:30,380
and wouldn't

213
00:08:30,940 --> 00:08:31,900
disrupt the ceremony.

214
00:08:32,660 --> 00:08:33,980
That's a great idea.

215
00:08:34,260 --> 00:08:36,580
Could you prepare some

216
00:08:36,820 --> 00:08:38,620
children's play facilities for us?

217
00:08:38,980 --> 00:08:39,940
Of course, Ms. Wen.

218
00:08:40,060 --> 00:08:41,500
We can arrange that anytime.

219
00:08:42,380 --> 00:08:43,020
Perfect.

220
00:08:44,900 --> 00:08:47,860
I've been a little worried
about the weather.

221
00:08:48,300 --> 00:08:50,540
